biography_text: NEWHOUSE, Daniel Milton, a Representative from Washington; born in Sunnyside, Yakima County, Wash., July 10, 1955; graduated from Sunnyside High School, Sunnyside, Wash., 1973; B.S., Washington State University, Pullman, Wash., 1977; farmer; member of the Washington state house of representatives, 2003-2009; director of the Washington state department of agriculture, 2009-2013; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Fourteenth and to the succeeding Congress (January 3, 2015-present).
